        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Bharath B M alias Preetham of Channasandra, India was able to abscond with a Toyota Fortuner, a Benelli motorcycle, and two Royal Enfield motorcycles before he was finally caught by police. The man had collected all kinds of keys while working as a mechanic at a dealership. What he would do is show up to take a car for a test drive, then when he returned give a key that looked like the original to the owner while retaining the key that goes to the car. Then he would return later and take the vehicle.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It took authorities doing some good gumshoe detective work to track the guy down, but he’s been brought to justice and all four vehicles were thankfully recovered.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Car scams and theft techniques don’t just stay in one part of the world anymore, so while reading about a guy stealing cars in southern India might not sound threatening to readers in North America, a similar scheme could easily be used around here. In other words, if you’re selling a car you need to be careful. This is just one of far too many scams out there.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "We keep pointing out that car thefts are high right now. Part of this is ",
